Karl,

Yes, diag is used internally to specify whether a constraint is 
algebraic or not.  An algebraic constraint like the one you are 
implementing should have diag[j] = 0. It is used to modify the 
steady-state Jacobian computed in class MultiJac to add the transient 
term on the diagonal of the Jacobian.  Take a look at method eval in 
class OneDim - this calls the eval methods of each domain, which each 
set the portions of the mask array (i.e., diag) relevant for that 
domain. This mask array is then used in updateTransient to modify the 
Jacobian for time stepping.  Hope this helps.

Dave


